{
    "key": "token_value_over_time",
    "name": "Token Value Over Time",
    "category": "Activity",
    "summary": "Measures wallet holdings for selected token and contract resources, with more weight for longer-held amounts. Contract selections resolve to their parent token while remaining independently selectable.",
    "description": "### What this algorithm is\nThis algorithm measures a wallet's token holdings for selected chain resources, giving more credit to tokens held longer.\n\nEach incoming transfer creates a separate lot. A new lot starts at zero value and gains value over time until it reaches full value after the maturation threshold.\n\n### How value is calculated\n- Each lot's age is measured in days.\n- Lot value grows linearly from 0 to 100% over the maturation threshold.\n- Once a lot reaches the threshold, it counts at full value.\n\nThe final wallet score is the sum of all remaining lot values across all selected resources after they are normalized to their parent token.\n\n### Multiple transfers\n- Every incoming transfer is a separate lot.\n- Outgoing transfers consume the oldest lots first (FIFO).\n- The algorithm evaluates remaining lots at the snapshot run time.\n\n### What data is used\nUpload one JSON file that provides the wallet addresses to score.\n\nExample:\n```json\n{\n  \"wallets\": {\n    \"ethereum\": [\"0x1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef12345678\"],\n    \"cardano\": [\"addr1q9exampleexampleexampleexampleexampleexample\"]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe algorithm reads indexed token transfer history from the database for the uploaded wallets only.\n\n### Resource selection\nSelect one or more supported resources under each chain.\n\n- Token resources represent the canonical synced token.\n- Contract resources stay independently selectable in presets, but they resolve to their parent token during sync and scoring.\n\n### Outputs\n- A per-wallet CSV with wallet_address and token_value.\n- A JSON details file with per-token and per-lot calculations.",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "inputs": [
        {
            "key": "wallets",
            "label": "Wallet Addresses JSON",
            "description": "Upload one JSON file with a wallets object containing ethereum and/or cardano wallet address arrays.",
            "type": "json",
            "required": true,
            "json": {
                "maxBytes": 5242880,
                "schema": "wallet_address_map",
                "rootKey": "wallets",
                "allowedChains": ["ethereum", "cardano"]
            }
        },
        {
            "key": "maturation_threshold_days",
            "label": "Maturation Threshold (Days)",
            "description": "Number of days a token lot must be held before it reaches full value.",
            "type": "integer",
            "min": 1,
            "max": 3650,
            "default": 90,
            "step": 1,
            "required": true,
            "uiHint": {
                "widget": "number",
                "suffix": "days",
                "presets": [7, 30, 90, 180, 365]
            }
        },
        {
            "key": "selected_resources",
            "label": "Resources to Include",
            "description": "Select one or more supported resources across chains. Contract selections are preserved in the preset and normalized to their parent token when building on-chain sync inputs and computing scores.",
